Citation.sAbstract: Densities and viscosities of l-proline and l-glutamine in aqueous metal electrolytes solution containing 0.06 and 0.10M Cu II nitrate and Ni II  chloride, have been determined experimentally at 308 K. The results obtained from density and viscosity measurements have been used to calculate  the apparent molar volume, ov, relative viscosity, crel, transfer volume o0  v(tr), at infinite dilution, free energy of activation of viscous flow of solvent   i0
Citation.sTitle: Volumetric and viscometric behaviour of amino acids in aqueous metal electrolytes solutions at 308K
